race.comment: ROSA AOTEAROA (3) returned a much improved galloper beaten a nose at Sale from the front. His two jumpouts were a good pointer to that and this looks winnable for him with average luck in the run. GOLDEN SPRITZ (2) also jumped out well and missed a nose here on debut. Jumped a 3.6F and the speed-bred gelding will also have taken fitness. He draws awkwardly as well but should be right in the finish. ALGADON STORM (6) was slow away at Sale first-up but was expected to need the run regardless. Her effort at Bendigo on debut was good in stronger and quick improvement is likely. OCTANE REIGN (5) didn't have the best of it at Moe on debut. Has jumped out well since and quick improvement is anticipated.
